to the AmazonFresh program, residents of Los Angeles, San Francisco, and Seattle can even order same-day deliveries of fresh, local groceries. Check out Groupon's collection for an Amazon coupon code that can save on these products and more.Amazon got its start in 1994 as a web-based bookseller, but quickly expanded its inventory to include almost every type of item imaginable, from apparel to housewares. Though its product base has grown, bookworms can still rely on Amazon for a good read. In fact, besides its trove of bound books, the site's extensive cache now includes digital reading content such as e-books that can be read on Amazon's Kindle reader. The Kindle Fire tablet, meanwhile, streams music, movies, and TV. And while you don't need an Amazon promo code to get great deals, even television fans seeking something new will be thrilled with Amazon's own original streaming content.Jeff Bezos, the founder of Amazon and "Time" magazine’s Person of the Year for 1999, named the company after the Amazon River. His reasoning was aspirational: the Amazon is one of the largest rivers in the world, and Bezos envisioned Amazon as becoming the largest store on earth. He and his team have achieved that goal, expanding their business worldwide by adding grocery delivery, restaurant delivery, steaming video and TV, streaming music, cloud-based storage, and the amazing line of Alexa-enabled Amazon devices. They’ve also embraced innovative marketing strategies such as allowing customers to rate products with negative reviews as well as positive ones. This transparent rating system, paired with Amazon’s comprehensive A-to-Z guarantee, has inspired trust and loyalty among consumers.How To Save Money At AmazonSaving money at Amazon is easy, and there are a lot of ways to do it. First, you can sign up for emails from Amazon, which will sometimes include exclusive Amazon promo codes. Some of these are for flash sales, so be sure to check your email promptly! You can also look up Amazon promo codes right here at Groupon Coupons to find special savings and Amazon discounts on beauty items, groceries, books, holiday cards, electronics, power tools, and more.Entering A Promo Code On Amazon.comIf you're entering a promo code on the Amazon website, you'll add partway through checkout. Once you have your order total and are about to finalize, look for the promotional code entry to put in your code and save more.Amazon Sales & Special OffersIf you sign up for emails from Amazon, you’ll be notified immediately about sales, discounts, and special offers.Ready to get Amazon’s electronics, books, and other products out of your computer screen and into your life? Head to Groupon’s collection of Amazon coupons and discount codes to save big on products and shipping.Using Groupon CouponsGroupon Coupons offers a variety of in-store coupons, online promo codes, and other special offers and sales. When you see a coupon that can be used as a printable in-store coupon or as an online promo code, it'll look like this:Promo codes that can be used online only will typically look like this:And finally, special sales will look like this:×About Amazon×Share this coupon with friends:    : How Coupons Work×How Coupons WorkWhen shopping other websites and stores, check out Groupon Coupons for exclusive coupon codes, free offers, and other giveaways. Here's how it works:Click on a couponWhen you click a coupon, a box appears with your coupon code.Note: If no code is required, your savings will automatically appear during checkout on the retailer's website.Shop the retailer's websiteClick the "Shop Online" button to visit the retailer's site and add items to your cart.Paste the coupon code at checkoutDuring checkout on the retailer's website, paste your code into the promo code field and complete your purchase.Click to Copy CodeGrouberGo to mobile siteAmazon Promo Code Discount: Up To 70% Off | Amazon Promo Codes & Coupons June 2017 | GrouponSearch GrouponZip Code, Neighb